    <h3 class="heading-medium">Optional and mandatory fields</h3>

    <div class="text">

      <ul class="list-bullet">
        <li>only ask for the information you absolutely need</li>
        <li>if you do ask for optional information, mark the labels of optional fields with '(optional)'</li>
        <li>don't mark mandatory fields with asterisks</li>
      </ul>

    </div>


    <!-- form labels -->
    <h3 class="heading-medium">Labels</h3>

    <p class="text">Click on the label &quot;Full name&quot; to bring focus to the form field.</p>

    <div class="example">
      <form>
        <label class="form-label" for="full-name-f1">Full name</label>
        <input class="form-control" id="full-name-f1" type="text">
      </form>
    </div>


    <!-- form spacing -->
    <h3 class="heading-medium">Spacing between form elements</h3>

    <p class="text">Ensure there is sufficient spacing between form elements.</p>

    <div class="example">
      <form>
        <div class="form-group">
          <label class="form-label" for="first-name-2">First name</label>
          <input class="form-control" id="first-name-2" type="text">
        </div>
        <div class="form-group">
          <label class="form-label" for="last-name-2">Last name</label>
          <input class="form-control" id="last-name-2" type="text">
        </div>
      </form>
    </div>


    <!-- hint text -->
    <h3 class="heading-medium">Hint text</h3>

    <ul class="list-bullet text">
      <li>don't use placeholder text in form fields, as this will disappear once content is entered into the form field</li>
      <li>use hint text for supporting contextual help, this will always be shown</li>
      <li>hint text should sit above a form field</li>
      <li>ensure hint text can be read correctly by screen readers</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="example">
      <form>
        <label class="form-label" for="ni-number">
          National Insurance number
          <span class="form-hint">It'll be on your last payslip. For example, JH 21 90 0A.</span>
        </label>
        <input class="form-control" id="ni-number" type="text">
      </form>
    </div>


    <!-- date inputs -->
    <h3 class="heading-medium">Date inputs</h3>

    <div class="example">

      <form>

        <fieldset>

          <legend class="form-label">Date of birth</legend>

          <div class="form-date">

            <p class="form-hint">For example, 31 3 1980</p>

          	<div class="form-group form-group-day">
          		<label for="dob-day">Day</label>
          		<input class="form-control" id="dob-day" type="number" pattern="[0-9]*" min="0" max="31">
          	</div>

          	<div class="form-group form-group-month">
          		<label for="dob-month">Month</label>
          		<input class="form-control" id="dob-month" type="number" pattern="[0-9]*" min="0" max="12">
          	</div>

          	<div class="form-group form-group-year">
          		<label for="dob-year">Year</label>
          		<input class="form-control" id="dob-year" type="number" pattern="[0-9]*" min="0" max="2014">
          	</div>

          </div>

        </fieldset>

      </form>

    </div>


    <!-- toggle date inputs -->
    <h3 class="heading-medium">Date inputs with inset form element</h3>

    <p>Insets can be used within forms to emphasise supporting information.</p>

    <p>Click on &quot;Yes&quot; to see how this works.</p>

    <div class="example">

      <div class="form-group form-group-compound">

        <form>

          <fieldset class="inline">

            <legend class="form-label">Is this person an owner?</legend>

            <div class="form-group form-group-compound">

              <label class="block-label" data-target="person-dob" for="radio-indent-1">
                <input id="radio-indent-1" name="radio-indent-group" value="Yes" type="radio">
                Yes
              </label>

              <label class="block-label" for="radio-indent-2">
                <input id="radio-indent-2" name="radio-indent-group" value="No" type="radio">
                No
              </label>

            </div>

            <div class="panel-indent js-hidden" id="person-dob">

              <div class="form-date">

                <label class="form-label">Date this person became an owner</label>

              	<div class="form-group form-group-day">
              		<label class="form-label" for="dob-day-2">Day</label>
              		<input class="form-control" id="dob-day-2" type="text">
              	</div>

              	<div class="form-group form-group-month">
              		<label class="form-label" for="dob-month-2">Month</label>
              		<input class="form-control" id="dob-month-2" type="text">
              	</div>

              	<div class="form-group form-group-year">
              		<label class="form-label" for="dob-year-2">Year</label>
              		<input class="form-control" id="dob-year-2" type="text">
              	</div>

              </div>

            </div>

          </fieldset>

        </form>

      </div>

    </div>


    <!-- drop down lists -->
    <h3 class="heading-medium">Drop-down lists</h3>

    <div class="text">
      <p>Avoid using drop-down lists (the HTML select element) - use radio buttons or checkboxes instead. (Preferred)</p>
      <p><a rel="external" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CUkMCQR4TpY">Watch Alice Bartlett present the failings of select boxes to meet the needs of less technically capable users</a>.</p>
      <p>Use as a last resort if there is an absolute need for it!</p>
    </div>

    <div class="example">

      <form>

        <label class="form-label" for="legal-status">Legal status</label>

        <select class="form-control-select" id="legal-status">
          <option>-- Please make a selection --</option>
          <option value="1">Charitable Interest Organisation</option>
          <option value="2">Community Interest Company</option>
          <option value="3">Government (Central)</option>
          <option value="4">Government Limited Liability Partnership</option>
        </select>

      </form>

    </div>


    <!-- search -->
    <h3 class="heading-medium">Search</h3>

    <div class="example">

      <form>

        <fieldset>

          <legend class="form-label">What are you looking for?</legend>

          <div class="form-search">

            <div class="form-group-search">
              <input class="form-control" id="search" type="search">
            </div>

            <div class="form-group-button">
              <button class="button" type="button">Search</button>
            </div>

          </div>

        </fieldset>

      </form>

    </div>


    <!-- textarea -->
    <h3 class="heading-medium">Textarea</h3>

		<div class="example">
  		<form>
        <label class="form-label" for="enquiry">Enquiry</label>
        <textarea class="form-control form-control-textarea" id="enquiry" rows="6" cols="50"></textarea>
  		</form>
		</div>


    <!-- radio buttons -->
    <h3 class="heading-medium">Radio buttons</h3>

    <div class="text">

      <ul class="list-bullet">
        <li>use these to let users choose a single option from a list</li>
        <li>for more than two options, radio buttons should be stacked</li>
        <li>radio buttons with large hit areas are easier to select with a mouse or touch devices</li>
      </ul>

    </div>

    <div class="example">

      <form>

        <fieldset class="inline">

          <legend class="form-label visuallyhidden">Do you know their National Insurance number?</legend>

          <div class="form-group form-group-compound">

            <label class="block-label" for="radio-inline-1">
              <input id="radio-inline-1" name="radio-inline-group" value="Yes" type="radio"> Yes
            </label>

            <label class="block-label" for="radio-inline-2">
              <input id="radio-inline-2" name="radio-inline-group" value="No" type="radio"> No
            </label>

          </div>

        </fieldset>

      </form>

    </div>

    <div class="example">

      <form>

        <label class="block-label" for="radio-1">
          <input id="radio-1" name="radio-group" value="Northern Ireland" type="radio">
          Northern Ireland
        </label>

        <label class="block-label" for="radio-2">
          <input id="radio-2" name="radio-group" value="Isle of Man or the Channel Islands" type="radio">
          Isle of Man or the Channel Islands
        </label>

        <p class="form-block">or</p>

        <label class="block-label" for="radio-3">
          <input id="radio-3" name="radio-group" value="I am a British citizen living abroad" type="radio">
          I am a British citizen living abroad
        </label>

      </form>

    </div>


    <!-- checkboxes -->
    <h3 class="heading-medium">Checkboxes</h3>

    <div class="text">

      <ul class="list-bullet">
        <li>use these to select either on/off toggles or multiple selections</li>
        <li>make it clear with words when users can select one or multiple options</li>
      </ul>

    </div>

    <div class="example">
      <form>
        <fieldset>
          <legend class="form-label-bold">Which types of waste do you transport regularly?</legend>
          <p>Select all that apply</p>
          <label class="block-label" for="checkbox-1">
            <input id="checkbox-1" value="waste-animal" type="checkbox">
            Waste from animal carcasses
          </label>
          <label class="block-label" for="checkbox-2">
            <input id="checkbox-2" value="waste-mines" type="checkbox">
            Waste from mines or quarries
          </label>
          <label class="block-label" for="checkbox-3">
            <input id="checkbox-3" value="farm-agricultural" type="checkbox">
            Farm or agricultural waste
          </label>
        </fieldset>
      </form>
    </div>

    <p>Large hit areas aren't always appropriate.</p>

    <div class="example">
      <form>
        <label class="form-label" for="telephone-number">Enter your telephone number</label>
          <input class="form-control" id="telephone-number" type="text">
          <label class="form-checkbox" for="checkbox-telephone-number">
          <input id="checkbox-telephone-number" value="checkbox-telephone-number" type="checkbox">
          I need to be contacted using a text phone
        </label>
      </form>
    </div>


    <!-- inset form elements -->
    <h3 class="heading-medium">Inset form elements</h3>

    <p>Insets can be used within forms to emphasise supporting information.</p>

    <p>Click on &quot;Yes&quot; to see how this works.</p>

    <div class="example">

      <form>

        <fieldset class="inline">

          <legend class="form-label">Do you know their National Insurance number?</legend>

          <div class="form-group form-group-compound">

            <label class="block-label" data-target="example-ni-number" for="radio-indent-3">
              <input id="radio-indent-3" name="radio-indent-group" value="Yes" type="radio">
              Yes
            </label>

            <label class="block-label" for="radio-indent-4">
              <input id="radio-indent-4" name="radio-indent-group" value="No" type="radio">
              No
            </label>

          </div>

          <div class="panel-indent js-hidden" id="example-ni-number">
            <label class="form-label" for="national-insurance">National Insurance number</label>
            <input class="form-control" id="national-insurance" type="text">
          </div>

        </fieldset>

      </form>

    </div>


    <p>Click on &quot;Citizen of a different country&quot; to see how this works.</p>


    <div class="example">

      <form>

        <fieldset>

          <legend class="form-label-bold">What is your nationality?</legend>

          <p>Select all options that are relevant to you.</p>

          <div class="form-group form-group-compound">

            <label class="block-label" for="nationality-british">
              <input type="checkbox" id="nationality-british" value="British">
              British (including English, Scottish, Welsh and Northern Irish)
            </label>

            <label class="block-label" for="nationality-irish">
              <input type="checkbox" id="nationality-irish" value="Irish">
              Irish
            </label>

            <label class="block-label" data-target="different-country" for="nationality-other">
              <input type="checkbox" id="nationality-other" value="Citizen of a different country">
              Citizen of a different country
            </label>

          </div>

          <div id="different-country" class="panel-indent js-hidden">
            <label class="form-label" for="nationality-other-country">Country name</label>
            <input class="form-control" type="text" id="nationality-other-country">
          </div>

      </form>

    </div>


    <!-- button -->
    <h2 class="heading-large">Buttons</h2>

    <h3 class="heading-medium">Button text</h3>

    <p class="text">Buton text should be short and describe the action the button performs.</p>


    <div class="example">
      <button class="button" type="button">Save and continue</button>
    </div>


    <p class="text">Launch your service with a Start now button.</p>


    <!-- start now -->
    <div class="example">
      <button class="button button-get-started" type="button">Start now</button>
    </div>


    <p class="text">Align the primary action button to the left edge of your form, in the user's line of sight.</p>


    <div class="example">

      <form class="form" method="post" action="/">

        <div class="form-group">
          <label class="form-label" for="form-email-address-1">Email address</label>
          <input class="form-control" type="text" id="form-email-address-1">
        </div>

        <div class="form-group">
          <button class="button">Save and continue</button>
          <p><a href="#">Back</a></p>
        </div>

      </form>

    </div>


    <!-- disabled button -->
    <h3 class="heading-medium">Disabled buttons</h3>

    <p>Disabled buttons should be set at 50% opacity.</p>

    <div class="example">
      <button class="button" type="button" disabled="disabled">Primary button</button>
    </div>








